<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="106" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.244/8–3044</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-05">September 5,
                                        1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the
                                President</hi></p>
                            <p rend="flushleft">[Subject:] British Beef Purchases</p>
                            <p>We have been informed by Marvin Jones that we will soon have
                                substantial supplies of so-called commercial and utility grades of
                                beef which can be made available to the British. I therefore suggest
                                that when you see the Prime Minister you discuss the possibility of
                                British reduction of purchases from Argentina in the amount that we
                                may be able to allocate from our supplies. It is believed that with
                                supplies that we can make available, a considerable reduction of
                                British meat purchases from Argentina may be entirely feasible.</p>
                            <closer><signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>